# CONTRACT 0 — PRE-COMMIT AUDIT

**This rule is ALWAYS active. The agent MUST follow it before every commit.**

## Golden rule

**Never commit partial changes.** Before every `git commit`, the agent must audit the ENTIRE repository as if building it from scratch. If something is stale, broken, or inconsistent — fix it BEFORE committing.

## Pre-commit checklist

The agent MUST complete ALL items before running `git add` / `git commit`:

### 1. No test/temp data in source files

- [ ] `ai-ds-spec.json` contains the ORIGINAL project palette, not test extraction results
- [ ] `ai-ds-styles.json` contains the ORIGINAL project palette
- [ ] No `*.backup.json`, `*.extracted.json`, `*.zip` in staged files (they must be in `.gitignore`)
- [ ] No `.cursor/debug-*.log` in staged files

### 2. Modular spec consistency

- [ ] `ai-ds-styles.json` exists and tokens match `ai-ds-spec.json` tokens section
- [ ] `ai-ds-components.json` exists and matches `ai-ds-spec.json` components array
- [ ] `ai-ds-blocks.json` exists and matches `ai-ds-spec.json` blocks array
- [ ] If any of the 3 module files changed, `ai-ds-spec.json` was rebuilt via `merge-spec.ts`

### 3. No duplicate cursor rules

- [ ] `projects/*/. cursor/rules/` directories do NOT contain copies of root-level rules
- [ ] All CONTRACT files exist ONLY in `.cursor/rules/` (root level)
- [ ] No two `.mdc` files have the same contract name

### 4. Cross-reference integrity

- [ ] Every script mentioned in CONTRACT files exists in `packages/core/scripts/`
- [ ] Every npm script in rules exists in `packages/core/package.json`
- [ ] CONTRACT 4, 5, 6, 7 all reference the modular workflow (ai-ds-styles.json + merge-spec)
- [ ] No CONTRACT references "edit ai-ds-spec.json directly" for style changes

### 5. .gitignore covers all temp artifacts

- [ ] `*.backup.json` is in `.gitignore`
- [ ] `*.extracted.json` is in `.gitignore`
- [ ] `*.zip` is in `.gitignore`
- [ ] `.cursor/debug-*.log` is in `.gitignore`

### 6. Package.json scripts are complete

- [ ] `spec:split`, `spec:merge`, `spec:validate`, `spec:validate-styles`, `spec:extract` — all present
- [ ] No broken script references

### 7. Git status is clean after commit

- [ ] Run `git status` after commit — must show `nothing to commit, working tree clean`
- [ ] If files reappear as modified (CRLF issue), they were not real changes — verify with `git diff`

## Dependency map

When changing a file on the LEFT, you MUST check/update files on the RIGHT:

```
CHANGED                          → CHECK / UPDATE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ai-ds-styles.json                → run merge-spec.ts → ai-ds-spec.json
ai-ds-components.json            → run merge-spec.ts → ai-ds-spec.json
ai-ds-blocks.json                → run merge-spec.ts → ai-ds-spec.json
extract-styles.ts                → CONTRACT 7 (references)
merge-spec.ts / split-spec.ts   → CONTRACT 6, CONTRACT 7 (pipeline description)
validate-spec.ts                 → CONTRACT 7 (validation step)
Any CONTRACT file                → check no duplicate in projects/*/
package.json (scripts)           → all CONTRACT files that reference npm scripts
.gitignore                       → verify temp files are excluded
```

## Forbidden actions

1. **NEVER commit test extraction results** (palette from a test URL) into source files
2. **NEVER leave duplicate rules** in `projects/*/` subdirectories
3. **NEVER edit `ai-ds-spec.json` tokens directly** — use `ai-ds-styles.json` + `merge-spec.ts`
4. **NEVER `git add .` blindly** — always review `git status` and `git diff --stat` first
5. **NEVER skip the checklist** — even for "small changes"

## How to run the audit

```bash
# 1. Check for temp files that shouldn't be committed
git status

# 2. Validate spec consistency
cd packages/core
npx tsx scripts/validate-spec.ts --styles-only

# 3. Check for duplicate rules
ls projects/*/.cursor/rules/ 2>$null

# 4. Verify gitignore
git ls-files --ignored --exclude-standard
```
